    "subject": "Fails to load in fullscreen mode",
    "description": "In some Linux distributions, the game fails to load in fullscreen mode. This seems to happen with some distribution only, and only with some architecture (32 bit).\r\n\r\nSee forum post \"here\":https://dev.etlegacy.com/boards/2/topics/2995?r=3007\r\n\r\n> Fullscreen is broken - The reason I was getting black screen before when I first tried the game was because no profile was set up and the game reverted to full screen causing it to crash.\r\n> By using version 2.72 I was able to create a profile, once this was done I was able to launch the latest version compiled from source with \"+set r_fullscreen 0 +set r_mode 3\"\r\n> this allowed the game to start windowed and can play on all servers, no problems just cannot use fullscreen mode. \"Windowed fullscreen\" works; I also tried changing the renderer but if fullsceen is selected it will go to a black screen until the revert settings timer counts down (does not crash).\r\n> If I try to start without a windowed mode enabled it will hang on a black screen as it did before with 2.75.\r\n\r\nThe issue happens on a SDL level. I'd suggest to use fullscreen windowed mode instead of fullscreen by default.",
